# Git commit author (mandatory)

When creating git commits in this repository:

1. **Author must be only `FishProgrammers`** — never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/agent co-author trailer.
2. **Do not append co-author lines** to commit messages, even if the IDE suggests it.
3. Commit messages: title + optional body only — no agent attribution footers.

The user wants GitHub to show a single committer: **FishProgrammers**.
